---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const translations = {
  en: '/privacy',
  'pt-br': '/pt-br/privacy',
};
---

<BaseLayout locale="en" title="Privacy Policy" translations={translations}>
  <article class="legal-page">
    <header class="legal-header">
      <p class="legal-meta">Effective date: March 31, 2026</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p>
        This website is a personal portfolio, blog, and notes site operated by Jonathan Tobias da Silva.
        This policy explains what information is collected when you use the site and how it is used.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>What this site collects</h2>
      <p>
        The site may collect limited usage data such as pageviews, referrers, top pages, device or browser information,
        and interactions with high-value contact actions such as CV downloads, email clicks, and outbound clicks to
        LinkedIn or GitHub.
      </p>
      <p>The site does not provide user accounts, comments, checkout flows, or direct file uploads.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Analytics and cookies</h2>
      <p>
        Analytics are used to understand traffic, content performance, and contact intent. Optional analytics are only
        activated after you make a consent choice through the site banner.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you accept analytics, the site may store a consent record in your browser and load a third-party analytics
        script. If you reject analytics, optional analytics are not loaded.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>How information is used</h2>
      <p>Collected information is used to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>understand which pages and topics are most useful to visitors</li>
        <li>measure interest in contact-oriented actions such as CV downloads and profile links</li>
        <li>maintain site performance, security, and content quality</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Third-party services</h2>
      <p>
        The site may rely on third-party services for analytics, hosting, and external links. When you click outbound
        links such as LinkedIn or GitHub, those services handle your information under their own policies.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        Analytics data is retained according to the configuration and retention rules of the analytics provider in use.
        Consent choices stored in your browser remain until you clear them or change your decision.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Your choices</h2>
      <p>
        You can reject optional analytics in the consent banner. You can also clear local browser storage or block
        cookies and third-party requests through your browser settings.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have a privacy question about this website, contact
        <a href="mailto:jonathantosilva@hotmail.com">jonathantosilva@hotmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-8);
  }

  .legal-header {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--space-3);
  }

  .legal-header h1,
  .legal-page h2 {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .legal-meta {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
</style>
